<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Cephalic region highly elevated near the middle, abruptly sloped downward posteriorly. Median ocular quadrangle wider behind than in front. Cephalothorax overlapping anterior abdomen. Sternum heart-shaped, pointed posteriorly, concave anteriorly below labium. Abdomen wider than long, with prominent coloration, three pairs of spines, and sigilla on dorsal and ventral sides. Four median sigilla arranged in trapezoid. Dorsal sigilla in three rows, situated near the anterior edge, posterior edge, and behind the posterior edge. Spinnerets encircled by a black sclerotized ring. IV femora elongated.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1833" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Gasteracantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gasteracantha" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Gasteracantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundevall, CJ" journalOrPublisher="Berling, Londini Gothorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B84" refString="Sundevall, CJ, 1833. Conspectus Arachnidum. C.F. Berling, Londini Gothorum" title="Conspectus Arachnidum. C. F." year="1833">Sundevall (1833)</bibRefCitation>
, and subsequently was revised by many authors (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1879.tb02656.x" author="Pickard-Cambridge, O" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="279 - 293" refId="B63" refString="Pickard-Cambridge, O, 1879. On some new and little known species of Araneidea, with remarks on the genus Gasteracantha. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 47 (2): 279 - 293, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1879.tb02656.x" title="On some new and little known species of Araneidea, with remarks on the genus Gasteracantha." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1879.tb02656.x" volume="47" year="1879">Pickard-Cambridge 1879</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahl, F" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="235 - 301" refId="B17" refString="Dahl, F, 1914. Die Gasteracanthen des Berliner Zoologischen Museums und deren geographische Verbreitung. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 7: 235 - 301" title="Die Gasteracanthen des Berliner Zoologischen Museums und deren geographische Verbreitung." volume="7" year="1914">Dahl 1914</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Benoit, PLG" journalOrPublisher="Annales, Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Sciences Zoologiques" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 70" refId="B5" refString="Benoit, PLG, 1962. Monographie des Araneidae - Gasteracanthinae africains (Araneae). Annales, Musee Royal de l'Afrique Centrale, Sciences Zoologiques 112: 1 - 70" title="Monographie des Araneidae - Gasteracanthinae africains (Araneae)." volume="112" year="1962">Benoit 1962</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Benoit, PLG" journalOrPublisher="Publicacoes Culturais da Companhia de Diamantes de Angola" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="41 - 52" refId="B6" refString="Benoit, PLG, 1964. Nouvelle contribution a la connaissance des Araneidae - Gasteracanthinae d'Afrique et de Madagascar (Araneae). Publicacoes Culturais da Companhia de Diamantes de Angola 69: 41 - 52" title="Nouvelle contribution a la connaissance des Araneidae - Gasteracanthinae d'Afrique et de Madagascar (Araneae)." volume="69" year="1964">1964</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Emerit, M" journalOrPublisher="Faune Madagascar" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 215" refId="B25" refString="Emerit, M, 1974. Arachnides araignees Araneidae Gasteracanthinae. Faune Madagascar 38: 1 - 215" title="Arachnides araignees Araneidae Gasteracanthinae." volume="38" year="1974">Emerit 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barrion, AT" journalOrPublisher="CAB International Wallingford, UK" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B4" refString="Barrion, AT, Litsinger, JA, 1995. Riceland Spiders of South and Southeast Asia. CAB International Wallingford, UK" title="Riceland Spiders of South and Southeast Asia." year="1995">Barrion and Litsinger 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Levi, HW" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="89 - 157" refId="B51" refString="Levi, HW, 1996. The American orb weavers Hypognatha, Encyosaccus, Xylethrus, Gasteracantha, and Enacrosoma (Araneae, Araneidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College 155: 89 - 157" title="The American orb weavers Hypognatha, Encyosaccus, Xylethrus, Gasteracantha, and Enacrosoma (Araneae, Araneidae)." volume="155" year="1996">Levi 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1833" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Gasteracantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gasteracantha" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Gasteracantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 88 valid species worldwide (
<bibRefCitation author="World Spider Catalog" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity and Conservation" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" publicationUrl="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" refId="B97" refString="World Spider Catalog, 2020. World Spider Catalog. Version 21.0. Natural History Museum Bern. http://wsc.nmbe.ch" title="World Spider Catalog. Version 21.0. Natural History Museum Bern." url="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" year="2020">World Spider Catalog 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
